==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Existential
<hw>Ex`is*ten"tial</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having existence.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark> <au>Bp.
Barlow.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>of or pertaining to, or having the character of,
existentialism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Logic)</fld> <def>specifying actual existence,
rather than only possibility; <as>as, the <ex>existential</ex>
operator</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p> --<wordforms><wf>Ex`is*ten"tial*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos>
<mark>[Archaic]</mark></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Existentially</qex> as well as essentially intelligent.</q>
<rj><qau>Colerige.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>existentialism</ent>⟦br⟧
